name: Atmosphere TV
description: Developed a custom component library and implemented automated testing using Vue 3, TailwindCSS, and StorybookJs for the internal and customer portals, and company website. Migrated, replaced, and rewrote 10+ libraries utilized in the customer portal from Vue 2 to Vue 3 JavaScript framework. Implemented two consumer interaction analytics tools for the customer portal using an in-house analytics API, HotJar, BigQuery, Looker, and Google Optimize

name: Longhorn Hack
description: Hosted the Longhorn Hack for Humanity, a one-day Hackathon with over 200 attendees catered towards beginners. Specifically coordinated the hacker experience by creating a seamless teammate matching experience.

name: Radix
description: Developed an invoice matching tool to assist the finance department in matching bills to invoice lists. The tool will create ~$12,000 in annual savings by improving process efficiency. Improved the timesheet tool for the project management team by streamlining the hour allocation process and creating a new web-admin management page. These improvements will result in annual cost savings of ~$43,000.

name: Flood Alert
description: Developed a website that serves as a platform that crowdsources information regarding flooded streets in communities and for people to communicate with one another and the broader community during an extreme weather situation. Developed a sensor to collect real-time, location-specific water level measurements and integrated it with the website. This sensor is currently in the testing phase. Presented the website and sensor at the 2nd annual Texas Steam Summit 2017 featuring MIT as well as the Houston City Council members.
